&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/standing/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/standing/> ;
  schema:name "Standing" ;
  schema:description "Standing is a triple (G, F, Φ) — an agent G, a forum F (a scene, normative system, or institutional context), and an act-class Φ — such that G holds a Hohfeldian privilege plus correlative right to perform acts of type Φ within F, and F's saturation nucleus takes G's acts of type Φ as valid inputs. The defining structure: standing is recognition by the forum's nucleus that G's outputs count. Without standing, G's acts enter H_t but do not propagate toward H*_t within F — they are formally valid acts that the forum simply does not process. Beck-Chevalley reading: the σ-Beck-Chevalley condition holds for standing in the forum hierarchy — standing in a forum F implies standing in every sub-forum F' ⊆ F for the same act-class (backward-stability: past recognition propagates). But the Δ-Beck-Chevalley condition fails at frontier forums — a forum at the boundary of its institutional scope may not yet commit to carrying G's standing forward in all extensions. Both conditions hold in the full institutional colimit. Minimum standing — standing every person holds in every legitimate forum simply by being a person — corresponds to a global section of the standing presheaf: a section that is present at every history and every sub-forum, stable under all restriction maps." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:isPartOf &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/> ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/standing/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "HohfeldianPosition, NormativeSystem, Act, Assertion, Report, Jurisdiction, Constitution, Person, Institution, Authority" ;
